         <cite class="fn">Lillian</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>      </div>
      
      <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://reviewsindepth.com/2010/03/twilight-the-anti-fan-and-the-culture-wars/comment-page-1/#comment-83">July 29, 2010 at 5:01 am</a></div>

      <p>I thought that the article was very well written, and I agree with alot of the points in it. </p>
<p>What I have noticed in my browsings of Anti forums is that alot of the Antis also would like to be writers themselves. Also, seeing as the major sucess as J.K. Rowling had, they have an incredibly high standard for writing, not only for themselves, but for published authors as well. (not nessecarily referring to content, but character development, showing not telling, etc.)</p>
<p>Also, a majority of the anti&#8217;s are actuly female, and not male.</p>

